Class Factor<SELF extends Factor<SELF>>

  • Type Parameters:
    SELF - is the generic type of the class itself (bound by the actual final subclass).
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Segment<Double>, AttributeReadMaximumValue<Double>, AttributeReadMinimumValue<Double>, AttributeReadValue<Double>, Datatype, SimpleDatatype<Double>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Alpha, Blue, Brightness, Chroma, ColorFactor, Green, Lightness, Red, Saturation

    public abstract class Factor<SELF extends Factor<SELF>>
extends AbstractDoubleSegment<SELF>
    The implementation of Segment for a factor in the range from 0 to 1 such as Saturation, Lightness, or Brightness.
    ATTENTION:
    Beside percent notation the String constructor both accepts byte values as well as factor notation.
    Since:
    1.0.0
    Author:
    Joerg Hohwiller (hohwille at users.sourceforge.net)
